🔁 Kubernetes Services

ClusterIP

Internal communication only

Gives service a stable internal IP



---

NodePort

Exposes service using: NodeIP:Port



---

LoadBalancer

Exposes service externally

Creates cloud load balancer



---

🚦 Ingress

Smart routing layer

Routes based on:

host

path



💡 Important:

Traffic does NOT go through rules

Controller reads rules and decides



---

🔗 Service Concept

Service is NOT a real server

It’s an abstraction

Uses kube-proxy for routing



---

⚙️ kube-proxy

Routes traffic from service → pods

Can send traffic:

same node

different node




---

☁️ AWS Networking

VPC

Isolated network

All resources inside it



---

Subnets

Public Subnet

Has Internet Gateway

Used for Load Balancer


Private Subnet

No direct internet access

Used for:

worker nodes

control plane




---

🌍 Internet Gateway

Attached to VPC

Enables internet access



---

🔁 NAT Gateway

Purpose:

Allow private subnet to access internet


Flow: Private → Internet ✅
Internet → Private ❌


---

🔐 Security Groups

Firewall per resource

Controls:

inbound traffic

outbound traffic



Example:

80 → HTTP

443 → HTTPS

6443 → Kubernetes API



---

🔑 IAM

Controls permissions between AWS services


Example

Node:

can upload to S3

cannot read sensitive data


💡 Important: Even if node is hacked → access still restricted


---

